main event: On 1 May 1965, an unidentified object was observed in the sky over St Augustine, Florida.
interesting points: The object was first thought to be a satellite but then began to dim and disappear., The observation lasted for about 5 minutes., Multiple witnesses reported the sighting, noting it moved very quickly., The report was acknowledged by the Air Force, which indicated further investigation may be conducted., A hand-drawn diagram in the report illustrated the object's trajectory from northwest to southeast.
